<paragraph id="8BAE3688F308382D05C9FAF3C364C2C0" blockId="24.[130,775,1373,1424]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">VOUCHERS. — Five ZMB vouchers originated from Taberna, Sokodé and Misahohe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE3688F308382D05C9FA1FC359C1CC" blockId="24.[130,778,1456,1692]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
ORIGINAL DATA. — Four populations occur in 
<collectingCountry id="F3067618F308382D0720FA1CC0D5C299" box="[621,676,1457,1481]" name="Togo" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Togo</collectingCountry>
. The species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3067618F308382D0443FA66C333C2B3" box="[270,322,1483,1507]" name="Togo" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Togo</collectingCountry>
in 
<quantity id="4CE99B6DF308382D042CFA66C3B2C2B3" box="[353,451,1483,1507]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.032" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="km" value="5032.0">5.032 km</quantity>
2, that is 3% of the West African range (
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B79F308382D0587FA48C3E3C2AD" author="MALLON D. P. &amp; HOFFMANN M. &amp; GRAINGER M. J. &amp; HIBERT F. &amp; VAN VLIET N. &amp; MCGOWAN P. J. K." box="[202,402,1509,1533]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" refId="ref27809" refString="MALLON D. P., HOFFMANN M., GRAINGER M. J., HIBERT F., VAN VLIET N. &amp; MCGOWAN P. J. K. 2015. - An IUCN Situation Analysis of Terrestrial and Freshwater Fauna in West and Central Africa. Occasional Paper of the IUCN Species Survival Commission No. 54. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. x + 162 p." type="book" year="2015">
Mallon 
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D0453FA4BC321C2AD" box="[286,336,1509,1533]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Elephant populations are certainly present in Fazao Malkafassa and Oti-Keran forests (
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B79F308382D07D1F9ADC2CAC162" author="ATSRI H. &amp; ADJOSSOU K. &amp; TAGBI K. &amp; TCHANI W. &amp; SEGLA K. &amp; TEBONOU G. &amp; ADJONOU K. &amp; ABOUDOU M. &amp; KOUDANOU M. &amp; BANLA T. &amp; KOMBATE Y." pageId="24" pageNumber="225" refId="ref24307" refString="ATSRI H., ADJOSSOU K., TAGBI K., TCHANI W., SEGLA K., TEBONOU G., ADJONOU K., ABOUDOU M., KOUDANOU M., AGBETI M, BANLA T. &amp; KOMBATE Y. 2013. - Inventaire faunique et forestier, etude ecologique et caracteristique du parc national de Fazao Malfakassa. Rapport FFW / MERF Togo, 96 p." type="book" year="2013">
Atsri 
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D079AF9ACC17BC148" box="[727,778,1536,1560]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B79F308382D058AF9B7C3B4C162" author="SEGNIAGBETO G. H. &amp; ASSOU D. &amp; AKOUDEWOU A." box="[199,453,1562,1586]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" refId="ref29551" refString="SEGNIAGBETO G. H., ASSOU D. &amp; AKOUDEWOU A. 2014 b. - Dignostic sur le prelevement des gibiers dans les zones peripheriques du parc national de l'Oti-Keran. Rapport du projet ONG AGBO- ZEGUE &amp; UICN-PACO, 28 p." type="book" year="2014">
Segniagbeto 
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D0404F9B6C30BC162" box="[329,378,1562,1586]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
2014b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B79F308382D049DF9B7C067C162" author="SEGNIAGBETO G. H. &amp; ASSOU D. &amp; KOUDZO K. K. &amp; AKOUDEWOU A." box="[464,534,1562,1586]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" refId="ref29652" refString="SEGNIAGBETO G. H., ASSOU D., KOUDZO K. K. &amp; AKOUDEWOU A. 2015 b. - Contribution on the improvement of the primate status and distribution in Central and Southern Togo. Primates project AGBO-ZEGUE NGO &amp; CI, 55 p." type="book" year="2015">2015b</bibRefCitation>
). The annual migration of a group of elephants is usually observed between the West African complex of protected areas (W, Arly and Pendjari Park: WAP) and the complex of protected areas in 
<collectingCountry id="F3067618F308382D077AF9C7C01BC1D2" box="[567,618,1642,1666]" name="Togo" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Togo</collectingCountry>
(Oti-Mandouri and Oti-Keran).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30B6503F308382D05C9F97FC7C3C2BD" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAE3688F308382D05C9F97FC299C1BA" blockId="24.[130,776,1746,2028]" box="[132,232,1746,1772]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE3688F308382D05C9F95FC7C3C2BD" blockId="24.[130,776,1746,2028]" lastBlockId="24.[813,1458,1459,1517]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Although two species are in some instances accepted; 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D0BF308382D07D3F95FC2A8C07C" baseAuthorityName="Blumenbach" baseAuthorityYear="1797" class="Mammalia" family="Elephantidae" genus="Loxodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proboscidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="africana">
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D07D3F95FC2A8C07C" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Loxodonta africana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C114D0BF308382D0446F8BFC00DC07C" authority="(Matschie, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Matschie" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[267,636,1810,1836]" class="Mammalia" family="Elephantidae" genus="Loxodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Proboscidea" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cyclotis">
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D0446F8BFC3B0C07C" box="[267,449,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Loxodonta cyclotis</emphasis>
(Matschie, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF804B79F308382D07C5F8BFC2CFC01C" author="GRUBB P. &amp; GROVES C. P. &amp; DUDLEY J. P. &amp; SHOSHANI J." pageId="24" pageNumber="225" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref26541" refString="GRUBB P., GROVES C. P., DUDLEY J. P. &amp; SHOSHANI J. 2000. - Living African elephants belong to two species: Loxodonta africana (Blumenbach, 1797) and Loxodonta cyclotis (Matschie, 1900). Elephant 2: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2000">
Grubb 
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D079BF8BFC171C07C" box="[726,768,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
; Rocha 
<emphasis id="B965EA9AF308382D0442F89FC34EC01B" box="[271,319,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">et al.</emphasis>
2001), taxonomy of West African elephants is currently not yet resolved. Most Togolese elephants show intermediate morphological characteristics between savannah and forest elephants (
<figureCitation id="132A2A0DF308382D0411F83CC3DDC0FB" box="[348,428,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="24.[365,376,748,766]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,705]" captionTargetId="figure-347@24.[132,1455,214,705]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIG. 23. — Elephants from the borders between Burkina Faso and Togo. Photograph: Emmanuel Hema." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5393562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5393562/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
), but true forest elephants are also said to occur in the country and some have been exported to zoos abroad (i.e. three elephants to a Tunisian zoo; 
<figureCitation id="132A2A0DF308382D07E6F87CC08AC0BB" box="[683,763,2001,2027]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="24.[131,142,1278,1296]" captionTargetBox="[132,775,816,1234]" captionTargetId="figure-349@24.[132,775,812,1259]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIG. 24. — A forest elephant from Togo, exhibited at a Tunisian zoo. Photograph: Spartaco Gippoliti." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5393564" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5393564/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). A taxonomic reassessment of African elephants is urgently needed in West Africa, even for a sound conservation strategy.
</paragraph>
